flowPara.flowSpan: In nature, animals must often decide between exploiting a resource site or leave it to explore potentially better ones.

flowRoot.flowPara: Serotonin (5-HT) | 5-HT is a neuromodulator that has been implicated in a variety of functions involving persistence in exploiting a site for uncertain reward.
How does 5-HT contributes to decision making in an explore/exploit dilema?

flowPara.flowSpan: Does 5-HT regulate differentially the switch between exploitative and exploratory behaviors depending on the level of uncertainty?
Foraging bouts with different levels of uncertainty

flowRoot.flowPara: The Flipping Task | By licking, mice exploits either one of two spouts. At any given moment, only one spout delivers reward and can deplete stochastically. In turn the other spout becomes activates. Mice must infer the state of the spout it is exploiting (fresh or depleted) and run on the treadmill to switch between them.

Uncertainty and Stimulation | For all sessions, mice were stimulated during 5 seconds for 30% of the foraging bouts. Three different probabilistic protocols were tested: 90/30, 60/20 and 45/15. (x/y = probability of reward for each lick/ probability of state switching for each lick)
